Adar  ~ A terminal based MIDI File Player with remote OSC control.

From "A Comprehensive Dictionary of Musical Instruments", 1964 by
Sibyl Marcuse, an Adar is a Basque Cow Horn.


osc Commands:

/adar/exit
    Terminate application.
    
/adar/play
    Start playback of selected MIDI file.
    
/adar/stop
    Stop playback.
    
/adar/list
    Display media-list contents.
    
/adar/info
    Display details about currently selected MIDI file.
    
/adar/scan directory
    Load each MIDI file in directory into media-list.
    
/adar/select file
    Select file from media-list.



